<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-409-189  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 409 189.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Lasers andamp; Optronics  Jan 1990 v9 n1 p59(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>OFC '90: from multiple stars to simple splices. (the Conference onOptical Fiber Communications to be held in San Francisco on Jan22-26, 1990)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hecht, Jeff.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Conference on Optical Fiber Communications (OFC), to be heldin San Francisco on Jan 22-26, 1990, will have video over fiber asits theme and will reflect the growing interest in analogtransmission for putting more video signals onto fibers.andP;  Alsoevident is a shift toward technologies for signal distribution tomultiple points rather than point-to-point links such as the TAT-8transatlantic cable.andP;  Papers will be presented dealing directly orindirectly with video distribution issues: BellSouth's Heathrowfiber-to-home trial near Orlando, FL, is one dealing specificallywith system plans, while others discuss such advanced systemconcepts as coherent distribution networks, and such advancedcomponents as optical amplifiers.andP;  Over 40 technical sessions willinclude 45 invited papers, over 100 contributed papers, 35 posterpapers, 11 tutorials and 20 short courses.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Conferences and MeetingsLasersVideo SystemsTechnologyResearch and DevelopmentOptical CommunicationsLaser and Infrared CommunicationConference on Optical Fiber Communications.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Coherent transmission through 400 km of singlemode and two fiberamps. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>